      • store

        public <TValue> java.util.Optional<TValue> store​(@NonNull
                                                 @NonNull Target<?> target,
                                                 @NonNull
                                                 @NonNull java.lang.String key,
                                                 @NonNull
                                                 TValue value)
        Description copied from interface: ArtObjectContext
        Stores a value for the given Target and this ArtObjectContext. This means a unique key is generated from the Target.uniqueId() and ArtObjectContext.uniqueId() and will be appended by your key.

        Then the StorageProvider.set(String, Object) method is called and the data is persisted.

        Specified by:
        store in interface ArtObjectContext<TArtObject extends ArtObject>
        Type Parameters:
        TValue - type of the value
        Parameters:
        target - target to store value for
        key - storage key
        value - value to store
        Returns:
        an Optional containing the existing value
        See Also:
        StorageProvider.set(String, Object)

      • store

        public <TValue> java.util.Optional<TValue> store​(@NonNull
                                                 @NonNull Target<?> target,
                                                 @NonNull
                                                 @NonNull java.lang.String key,
                                                 @NonNull
                                                 @NonNull java.lang.Class<TValue> valueClass)
        Description copied from interface: ArtObjectContext
        Retrieves a persistently stored value from the StorageProvider and returns it cast to the given type. Will return an empty Optional if casting fails or the data does not exist.

        The data that is fetched will be stored under a unique key combination of ArtObjectContext.uniqueId() and Target.uniqueId().

        Specified by:
        store in interface ArtObjectContext<TArtObject extends ArtObject>
        Type Parameters:
        TValue - type of the value
        Parameters:
        target - target to store value for
        key - storage key
        valueClass - class of the value type you expect in return
        Returns:
        the stored value or an empty Optional if the value type cannot be cast or does not exist

      • storageKey

        public AbstractArtObjectContext<TArtObject> storageKey​(java.lang.String storageKey)
        Description copied from interface: ArtObjectContext
        Sets the unique storage key used to identify the context from which this art object was loaded.

        The key should be generated when the art object context is created and must stay the same to retrieve the stored data.

        Specified by:
        storageKey in interface ArtObjectContext<TArtObject extends ArtObject>
        Parameters:
        storageKey - the unique key of the load operation
        Returns:
        this art object context
